Quote: And I do hereby further proclaim ... that Her Majesty has been further pleased to appoint a Legislative Council for the said colony of New Zealand ... and to ... direct that such Legislative Council shall ... consist of ... His Excellency the Governor for the time being, the Colonial Secretary ..., the Attorney-General ..., the Colonial Treasurer ..
Notes: 1841 May 3 Governor Hobson's Proclamation in 1949 Rutherford ed. Select Documents 11(a)

